The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Carlo view
                                                                                                                       7                                      Carlo view
                      
	London: Chelsea manager Carlo Ancelotti says Ashley Cole will remain at the club for the forthcoming season. Ancelotti told the club website that Cole will be an important player for us next season. One hundred per cent.         
	The Italian was responding to speculation linking Cole with a move away from Stamford Bridge. Media reports have claimed Cole is a target for Real Madrid, whose new coach Jose Mourinho used to manage the defender. (AFP)                                                                                                                     
